org.jamsim.ascape.stats

Class CollectorFunction<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • StatCollectorCondCSA
      • org.jamsim.ascape.stats.CollectorFunction<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the scape member this collector gets data from.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CollectorFunctionPerIteration

    public class CollectorFunction<T>
extends StatCollectorCondCSA
    Collect data values on a subset of the scape. The subset to collect is defined by a function predicate. The value to collect is defined by a value function.
    Version:
    $Revision$
    Author:
    Oliver Mannion

        public CollectorFunction(java.lang.String name,
                 StatsFunction<T> valueFunction,

        Construct a CollectorFunction that returns values for all scape members. i.e: has no predicate.

      • CollectorFunction

        public CollectorFunction(java.lang.String name,
                 StatsFunction<T> valueFunction,
                 StatsPredicate<T> predicate,
                 MutableDouble denominator)
        Construct a CollectorFunction.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the value being collected
        valueFunction - value to collect from the scape members
        predicate - predicate to determine which scape members to collect data for. If null, collects data for all members.
        denominator - value to divide the sum by in getRatio().
